        <abstract>
            <p>Comments on letter from Jeffries Wyman.</p>
            <p>Discusses reprinting reviews by Asa Gray.</p>
            <p>Mentions views of W. S. Symonds on the geological record.</p>
            <p>Discusses descent of turtles and tortoises.</p>
            <p>The universality of variation.</p>
            <p>Notes only a few species leave modified descendants.</p> 
<p>Discusses <hi rend="italic">Apteryx</hi>.</p> 
            <p>Variation among pigeons.</p>
            <p>Comments on fertility among hybrids.</p>
            <p>Does not agree that he makes natural selection do too much work.</p>
        </abstract>
